  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\nFutures showing modest green despite Iran war escalation, with SPY up 1.01% to $711.21 and QQQ leading at +1.67%. Tech sector strength driving the bounce while VIX pullback to 29.55 suggests traders are getting numb to geopolitical noise.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Jobless Claims (12:30 ET)</strong> - Critical labor data with continuing claims in focus as recession fears persist</li>\n<li><strong>PMI Flash Readings (13:45 ET)</strong> - Manufacturing and services data will show if Iran war is hitting economic activity</li>\n<li><strong>Natural Gas Stocks (14:30 ET)</strong> - Energy storage data matters more with Middle East supply disruptions</li>\n<li><strong>Trump Approval Ratings</strong> - CNBC survey showing lowest approval on economy creates political risk overhang</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Iran's control over shipping strait after peace talks collapse is the real market mover - oil demand forecasts getting slashed but supply constraints remain</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\nTech (XLK +2.20%) and Energy (XLE +1.20%) leading pre-market as Iran conflict creates divergent winners. Real Estate (XLRE -0.73%) getting hammered on rate fears while Financials (XLF -0.17%) struggle despite higher yield environment.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Tech resilience shows fundamentals trumping geopolitics - if PMIs hold up, this breakout has legs to $720 SPY</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>VIX still elevated at 29.55 despite rally attempt - any disappointment in economic data triggers flush back to $700 support</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY $715</strong> - Key resistance from March highs, break confirms uptrend continuation</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ $660</strong> - Round number resistance, tech needs to clear for sustained rally</li>\n<li><strong>VIX $32</strong> - Reclaim signals fear trade back on, risk-off rotation</li>\n<li><strong>XLE $95</strong> - Energy sector breaking out of range, Iran premium play</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
